83.3	The_NeverEnding_Story_(film)	The NeverEnding Story (film)	The NeverEnding Story (German: ) is a 1984 German epic fantasy film based on the novel of the same name written by Michael Ende. The film was directed and co-written by Wolfgang Petersen (his first English-language film) and starred Barret Oliver, Noah Hathaway and Tami Stronach. At the time of its release, it was the most expensive film produced outside of the USA or the USSR. It was then followed by two sequels: The NeverEnding Story II: The Next Chapter and The NeverEnding Story III: Escape From Fantasia.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/9b/Neverendingstoryposter.jpg/220px-Neverendingstoryposter.jpg
